7 Section 1. R.S. 46:233.4 is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
8 §233.4. Verification of citizenship of applicants for public benefits
9 A. Except as prohibited by federal law, a state agency or political subdivision
10 shall verify that each applicant who applies for federal, state, or local public benefit
11 is a person who has been recognized as a citizen of the United States by birthright,
12 naturalization, or any other method provided for under applicable federal law or, has
13 satisfactory immigration status as a qualified alien as defined in 8 U.S.C. 1641(b) ,or
14 receives coverage pursuant to 42 U.S.C. 1396b(v)(4).
15 B. For the purposes of Medicaid, Medicare, the Supplemental Nutrition
16 Assistance Program (SNAP), and any health plan offered through the
17 Affordable Care Act marketplace, the term "qualified alien" shall be limited to:
18 (1) An alien lawfully admitted for permanent residence as an immigrant,
19 as defined in 8 U.S.C. 1101(a)(15) and 1101(a)(20), excluding alien visitors,
20 tourists, diplomats, students, and other individuals admitted temporarily
21 without intent to abandon a foreign residence.
22 (2) An alien granted the status of Cuban or Haitian entrant, as defined
